    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Brain Awareness Week is the global campaign to foster public enthusiasm and support for brain science. Every March, \u201cpartners host imaginative activities in their communities that share the wonders of the brain and the impact brain science has on our everyday lives\u201d.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Brain Awareness Week\u2019s 25th anniversary campaign has taken place from March 16-22, 2020 but unfortunately the majorities of the planned activities has been cancelled because Coronavirus 19 pandemic infection.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Universities are closed in many countries, with web teaching substitutions; people are requested to stay at home to slow the epidemic infection spreading; the hospitals are under stress because of the high number of patients in intensive care units requiring respiratory supports.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "In many hospitals, neurologic departments have been limited in their spaces, to host COVID-19 patients and all doctor community is involved in the care of this infections, that is much more severe in fragile patients, as those of old age, affected by neurodegenerative diseases.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "We don\u2019t have to forget the many doctors were infected and died : one of them was dr. Ivo Cillesi (61 years), an expert of Alzheimer\u2019s diseases, and one of the main supporter of the use of the \u201cdoll therapy\u201d to improve anxiety and give relaxation to Alzheimer\u2019s patients .",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "For this Brain Awareness Week\u2019s 25th anniversary , the Italian Society of Neurology (SIN) gave a title RIsinG the Brain inviting to divulgate all the news for therapy , care and diagnosis of the neurologic disorders.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Neurologic Sciences, as done in the past years, selected the most cited articles published in the past year and granted free access to them one month (Table 1).",
            "cite_spans": [],
